Japan May Postpone Income Tax Increase by One Year, Asahi Says

-- B y   T a k e h i k o   K u m a k u r a
-- 
2011-09-25T21:44:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/japan-may-postpone-income-tax-increase-by-one-year-asahi-says.html
Japan  may postpone a planned income
tax increase by one year, the Asahi newspaper reported, without
saying where it obtained the information. The governing
 Democratic Party  of Japan may propose implementing the tax
increase in January 2013, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  